data.title: Prime minister visits Finland
data.text: Tallinn, Stenbock House 23 January 2004 From next Monday, Prime Minister Juhan Parts will pay a two-day work visit to Finland at the invitation of his colleague Matti Vanhanen. On Monday, both prime ministers will make a presentation at a seminar to be held at the Osuuspankki Research Institute. Prime Minister Parts´ speech is entitled "Estonia, Finland, and the competitive European Union". The prime ministers will hold a meeting at 15.00 hours on Monday, followed by a press conference at 16.00 hours. They plan to discuss the cooperation between the two countries in the European Union, bilateral relations, and Finland´s experience in developing a knowledge-based economy. The discussion will also cover the Wise Men report about the two countries´ relations, which was finalised last year, and the activities arising from it. At 7.50 hours on Tuesday morning, the prime minister will give an interview to the YLE 1 morning programme. A meeting with Speaker of the Finnish Parliament Paavo Lipponen is schedule for 9.00 hours, and at 10.00 hours the prime minister will meet the President of Finland Tarja Halonen. Tuesday´s schedule also includes a visit to the Finnish National Technology Agency Tekes and the Innopol high-tech centre. Both Estonia and Finland consider it very important to develop R&D cooperation between the two countries. Prime Minister Parts will return to Estonia on Tuesday afternoon.
